<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-03-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-03-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="367" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d367">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Dawson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Bogota</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-03-01"><hi rend="italic">March 1,
                                1909</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Colombian minister at Washington has already telegraphed ratification by
                            the Senate of the United States. Opposition developing. The enemies (?)
                            of the President attacking the assembly, demanding elected Congress and
                            the amendment Jurado (?) clause. Ratification is certain unless Reyes
                            weakens. Final vote, it is hoped, by Friday.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>